      "comment_id" : 94614937,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Minor nit-pick: <code>var</code> is not a keyword! From the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se10/html/jls-3.html#jls-3.9\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JLS</a>: &quot;var is not a keyword, but rather an identifier with special meaning as the type of a local variable declaration&quot;. Thus, unlike keywords, there is nothing to stop you calling a variable or a method &quot;var&quot;."
